      "role": "user",
      "content": "i guess. it just feels like everything is so temporary, you know? you see these massive mountains and they've been here for millions of years, and then there's us, just passing through for a second. it feels kind of pointless to keep moving forward when you know the trip has to end anyway. i feel like i'm just waiting for the final stop.",
